説明

An internal interface that abstracts some DOMNode-related parts that both nsIContent and nsIDocument share. An instance of this interface has a list of nsIContent children and provides access to them.

nsINode.h の 265 行で定義されています。

列挙型

anonymous enum

Bit-flags to pass (or'ed together) to IsNodeOfType()

列挙型の値:
eCONTENT 

nsIContent nodes

eDOCUMENT 

nsIDocument nodes

eATTRIBUTE 

nsIAttribute nodes

eTEXT 

text nodes

ePROCESSING_INSTRUCTION 

xml processing instructions

eCOMMENT 

comment nodes

eHTML_FORM_CONTROL 

form control elements

eDOCUMENT_FRAGMENT 

document fragments

eDATA_NODE 

data nodes (comments, PIs, text). Nodes of this type always returns a non-null value for nsIContent::GetText()

eMEDIA 

HTMLMediaElement

eANIMATION 

animation elements

eFILTER 

filter elements that implement SVGFilterPrimitiveStandardAttributes

nsINode.h の 338 行で定義されています。

       {
    eCONTENT             = 1 << 0,
    eDOCUMENT            = 1 << 1,
    eATTRIBUTE           = 1 << 2,
    eTEXT                = 1 << 3,
    ePROCESSING_INSTRUCTION = 1 << 4,
    eCOMMENT             = 1 << 5,
    eHTML_FORM_CONTROL   = 1 << 6,
    eDOCUMENT_FRAGMENT   = 1 << 7,
    eDATA_NODE           = 1 << 8,
    eMEDIA               = 1 << 9,
    eANIMATION           = 1 << 10,

  };

void nsINode::AddMutationObserver ( nsIMutationObserver *  aMutationObserver)

Adds a mutation observer to be notified when this node, or any of its descendants, are modified. The node will hold a weak reference to the observer, which means that it is the responsibility of the observer to remove itself in case it dies before the node. If an observer is added while observers are being notified, it may also be notified. In general, adding observers while inside a notification is not a good idea. An observer that is already observing the node must not be added without being removed first.

nsINode.h の 824 行で定義されています。

参照先 nsAutoTObserverArray< T, N >::IndexOf(), nsINode::nsSlots::mMutationObservers, NS_ASSERTION, と Slots().

  {
    nsSlots* s = Slots();
    NS_ASSERTION(s->mMutationObservers.IndexOf(aMutationObserver) ==
                 nsTArray<int>::NoIndex,
                 "Observer already in the list");
    s->mMutationObservers.AppendElement(aMutationObserver);
  }

関数の呼び出しグラフ:

void nsINode::AddMutationObserverUnlessExists ( nsIMutationObserver *  aMutationObserver)

Same as above, but only adds the observer if its not observing the node already.

    s->mMutationObservers.AppendElementUnlessExists(aMutationObserver);
  }

nsresult nsINode::AppendChildTo ( nsIContent *  aKid,
bool  aNotify 
)

Append a content node to the end of the child list. This method handles calling BindToTree on the child appropriately.

引数:
aKidthe content to append
aNotifywhether to notify the document (current document for nsIContent, and |this| for nsIDocument) that the append has occurred
例外:
NS_ERROR_DOM_HIERARCHY_REQUEST_ERRif one attempts to have more than one element node as a child of a document. Doing this will also assert -- you shouldn't be doing it! Check with nsIDocument::GetRootElement() first if you're not sure. Apart from this one constraint, this doesn't do any checking on whether aKid is a valid child of |this|.
NS_ERROR_OUT_OF_MEMORYin some cases (from BindToTree).

nsINode.h の 571 行で定義されています。

  {
    return InsertChildAt(aKid, GetChildCount(), aNotify);

virtual nsresult nsINode::Clone ( nsINodeInfo *  aNodeInfo,
nsINode **  aResult 
) const [pure virtual]

Clones this node. This needs to be overriden by all node classes. aNodeInfo should be identical to this node's nodeInfo, except for the document which may be different. When cloning an element, all attributes of the element will be cloned. The children of the node will not be cloned.

引数:
aNodeInfothe nodeinfo to use for the clone
aResultthe clone

virtual nsIContent* const* nsINode::GetChildArray ( uint32_t *  aChildCount) const [pure virtual]

Get a raw pointer to the child array. This should only be used if you plan to walk a bunch of the kids, promise to make sure that nothing ever mutates (no attribute changes, not DOM tree changes, no script execution, NOTHING), and will never ever peform an out-of-bounds access here. This method may return null if there are no children, or it may return a garbage pointer. In all cases the out param will be set to the number of children.

mozilla::dom::FragmentOrElement, と mozilla::dom::MOZ_FINALで実装されています。

参照元 GetLastChild().

呼出しグラフ:

  {
    // Make sure that we get the owner document of the content node, in case
    // we're in document teardown.  If we are, it's important to *not* use
    // globalObj as the node's parent since that would give the node the
    // principal of globalObj (i.e. the principal of the document that's being
    // loaded) and not the principal of the document that's being unloaded.
    // See http://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=227417
    return OwnerDoc();
  }

呼出しグラフ:

nsIContent* nsINode::GetPreviousContent ( const nsINode *  aRoot = nullptr) const

Get the previous nsIContent in the pre-order tree traversal of the DOM. If aRoot is non-null, then it must be an ancestor of |this| (possibly equal to |this|) and only nsIContents that are descendants of aRoot, including aRoot itself, will be returned. Returns null if there are no more nsIContents to traverse.

nsINode.h の 1205 行で定義されています。

参照先 GetLastChild(), GetParent(), GetParentNode(), GetPreviousSibling(), と NS_ASSERTION.

  {
      // Can't use nsContentUtils::ContentIsDescendantOf here, since we
      // can't include it here.
#ifdef DEBUG
      if (aRoot) {
        const nsINode* cur = this;
        for (; cur; cur = cur->GetParentNode())
          if (cur == aRoot) break;
        NS_ASSERTION(cur, "aRoot not an ancestor of |this|?");
      }
#endif

    if (this == aRoot) {
      return nullptr;
    }
    nsIContent* cur = this->GetParent();
    nsIContent* iter = this->GetPreviousSibling();
    while (iter) {
      cur = iter;
      iter = reinterpret_cast<nsINode*>(iter)->GetLastChild();
    }
    return cur;
  }

nsIContent* nsINode::GetSelectionRootContent ( nsIPresShell *  aPresShell)

Get the nearest selection root, ie. the node that will be selected if the user does "Select All" while the focus is in this node. Note that if this node is not in an editor, the result comes from the nsFrameSelection that is related to aPresShell, so the result might not be the ancestor of this node. Be aware that if this node and the computed selection limiter are not in same subtree, this returns the root content of the closeset subtree.

nsIDocument* nsINode::OwnerDoc ( ) const

Return the "owner document" of this node. Note that this is not the same as the DOM ownerDocument -- that's null for Document nodes, whereas for a nsIDocument GetOwnerDocument returns the document itself. For nsIContent implementations the two are the same.

nsINode.h の 470 行で定義されています。

参照元 ElementDependentRuleProcessorData::ElementDependentRuleProcessorData(), GetCurrentDoc(), GetOwnerDocument(), nsIContent::IsInHTMLDocument(), mozilla::dom::Element::MozRequestPointerLock(), MOZ_FINAL< T >::nsRange(), OwnerDocAsNode(), mozilla::dom::Element::RegisterFreezableElement(), と mozilla::dom::Element::UnregisterFreezableElement().

  {
    return mNodeInfo->GetDocument();
  }

) [protected]
virtual void nsINode::RemoveChildAt ( uint32_t  aIndex,
bool  aNotify 
) [pure virtual]

Remove a child from this node. This method handles calling UnbindFromTree on the child appropriately.

引数:
aIndexthe index of the child to remove
aNotifywhether to notify the document (current document for nsIContent, and |this| for nsIDocument) that the remove has occurred

Note: If there is no child at aIndex, this method will simply do nothing.

mozilla::dom::MOZ_FINAL, mozilla::dom::FragmentOrElement, mozilla::dom::MOZ_FINAL, mozilla::dom::MOZ_FINAL, mozilla::dom::MOZ_FINAL, と mozilla::dom::MOZ_FINALで実装されています。

nsINode* nsINode::SubtreeRoot ( ) const

Get the root of the subtree this node belongs to. This never returns null. It may return 'this' (e.g. for document nodes, and nodes that are the roots of disconnected subtrees).

nsINode.h の 776 行で定義されています。

参照先 GetParentNode(), IsInDoc(), mSubtreeRoot, node, NS_ASSERTION, と OwnerDocAsNode().

参照元 nsIContent::IsInAnonymousSubtree().

  {
    // There are three cases of interest here.  nsINodes that are really:
    // 1. nsIDocument nodes - Are always in the document.
    // 2. nsIContent nodes - Are either in the document, or mSubtreeRoot
    //    is updated in BindToTree/UnbindFromTree.
    // 3. nsIAttribute nodes - Are never in the document, and mSubtreeRoot
    //    is always 'this' (as set in nsINode's ctor).
    nsINode* node = IsInDoc() ? OwnerDocAsNode() : mSubtreeRoot;
    NS_ASSERTION(node, "Should always have a node here!");
#ifdef DEBUG
    {
      const nsINode* slowNode = this;
      const nsINode* iter = slowNode;
      while ((iter = iter->GetParentNode())) {
        slowNode = iter;
      }

      NS_ASSERTION(slowNode == node, "These should always be in sync!");
    }
#endif
    return node;
  }

virtual JSObject* nsINode::WrapNode ( JSContext *  aCx,
JS::Handle< JSObject * >  aScope 
) [protected, virtual]

WrapNode is called from WrapObject to actually wrap this node, WrapObject does some additional checks and fix-up that's common to all nodes. WrapNode should just call the DOM binding's Wrap function.
